# Ledger roots for the unified cost tracker. One path per line.
# Copy this file to roots.conf and edit paths for your machine:
#   cp roots.conf.example roots.conf
# install.sh generates roots.conf for you if it is missing.
#
# The FIRST listed root is "primary": prices.json + monthly/ archive live there.
# Lines starting with # are comments; blank lines are ignored.
# Runtime overrides (no edit needed):
#   PI_COST_LEDGERS=/path/a:/path/b   (PATH-style, colon-separated)
#   PI_COST_LEDGER=/path/a            (legacy: single root only)

# Primary: host pi (scripts, prices, and archive live here).
~/.pi/cost-tracker

# Optional: a second pi environment that also produces a ledger.
# Example: construct-cli sandbox home. Add/remove lines for your setup.
# The host scripts read every root listed here and report a COMBINED total;
# ledgers must be disjoint (each call logged once) for an accurate sum.
# ~/.config/construct-cli/home/.pi/cost-tracker
